Thank you for your kind remarks regarding this site Eric, much appreciated.
Rochambeau was very young at Laufeldt and was wounded while leading a battalion of the La Marche Regiment during the first attack. He could not have cheered on the Auvergne Regiment as they were in reserve and never actually saw action.
I have more details on troop formations which I will forward later.
Best wishes and good luck with your article.
Graham]]></description>
