					<description><![CDATA[Hi Graham
 wonderful site! I teach history and write for a number of American history publications. Now doing Laufeldt-- and have come up with a problem-- the Comte de Rochambeau of American Revolution fame was wounded twice in that battle-- he was colonel of the Regiment de la Marche, yet there is NO reference to that Regiment at Laufeldt--yet there is a passing mention of him with the Auvergne Regiment, cheering them on&quot;--and evenyour map shows the Auvegne were there-at Laufeldt--I am writing an article-- any thoughts on this?-]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi Graham<br />
 wonderful site! I teach history and write for a number of American history publications. Now doing Laufeldt&#8211; and have come up with a problem&#8211; the Comte de Rochambeau of American Revolution fame was wounded twice in that battle&#8211; he was colonel of the Regiment de la Marche, yet there is NO reference to that Regiment at Laufeldt&#8211;yet there is a passing mention of him with the Auvergne Regiment, cheering them on&#8221;&#8211;and evenyour map shows the Auvegne were there-at Laufeldt&#8211;I am writing an article&#8211; any thoughts on this?-</p>
