					<description><![CDATA[Hello Graham, 

Love your site! I used your site to prepare for my visits to Koniggratz and Austerlitz a few years ago.  

After nearly 30 years of exploring battlefields all over the world, I have finally started gathering all my notes, photos, maps, letters, social media posts, documents etc in one place. 

My new website is www.battlefieldtravels.com  and is a travel blog focused on battlefields and a virtual museum.  Eventually there will be hundreds of battlefield studies on there as I work my way through.

Given that our audiences will overlap, I thought it would be useful to post links to each other&#039;s websites as &#039;further reading&#039; or &#039;recommended websites&#039;. 

Let me know what you think,

Mick]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hello Graham, </p>
<p>Love your site! I used your site to prepare for my visits to Koniggratz and Austerlitz a few years ago.  </p>
<p>After nearly 30 years of exploring battlefields all over the world, I have finally started gathering all my notes, photos, maps, letters, social media posts, documents etc in one place. </p>
<p>My new website is <a href="http://www.battlefieldtravels.com" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.battlefieldtravels.com</a>  and is a travel blog focused on battlefields and a virtual museum.  Eventually there will be hundreds of battlefield studies on there as I work my way through.</p>
<p>Given that our audiences will overlap, I thought it would be useful to post links to each other&#8217;s websites as &#8216;further reading&#8217; or &#8216;recommended websites&#8217;. </p>
<p>Let me know what you think,</p>
<p>Mick</p>
